subclause.amendment:
AMENDMENT: replace Item 4.0 spec command with vikunja_mcp-only kill, preceded by a Get-Process Claude empty check (verifies LA prep-2 attestation):

```powershell
# Step 1: verify LA prep-2 attestation honored (other AI surfaces closed BEFORE EA-8 spawn)
$claudeProcs = Get-Process -Name "Claude" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
if ($claudeProcs) {
  throw "Claude Desktop processes still running ($($claudeProcs.Count) PIDs). LA prep-2 attestation was 'Other AI surfaces closed' but Claude.exe found. Close Claude Desktop manually before continuing."
}
Write-Host "Claude Desktop process check: empty (prep-2 honored)."

# Step 2: kill any python processes holding vikunja_mcp module loaded.
# This is the actual functional requirement — release file locks on tools/vikunja_mcp/ before MCP config rewrites.
# Get-Process has no CommandLine property; must use Get-CimInstance per F1/F2 fix.
$vikunjaMcpProcs = Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "Name = 'python.exe'" |
  Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -match 'vikunja_mcp' }
if ($vikunjaMcpProcs) {
  $vikunjaMcpProcs | ForEach-Object {
    Write-Host "Stopping vikunja_mcp python (PID $($_.ProcessId)): $($_.CommandLine)"
    Stop-Process -Id $_.ProcessId -Force
  }
} else {
  Write-Host "No vikunja_mcp python processes found (already stopped or not loaded this session)."
}

# Step 3: verify post-kill (no vikunja_mcp pythons remain)
Start-Sleep -Milliseconds 500  # let process termination propagate
$remaining = Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "Name = 'python.exe'" |
  Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -match 'vikunja_mcp' }
if ($remaining) {
  throw "vikunja_mcp python processes still running post-kill ($($remaining.Count) remain). Investigate before continuing."
}
Write-Host "Item 4.0 NARROWED kill complete: vikunja_mcp pythons released; Claude Desktop confirmed closed."
```

DROPPED from spec: `Get-Process -Name "Claude","Code" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force` — this was the source of the CC-1 self-termination cascade and is redundant with LA prep-2.

EA-8 NOTE: the Stage 4 XML's Item 4.0 description ("Close Claude Desktop, all VS Code windows, Claude Code terminals") is interpreted via this narrowing: those surfaces are LA-closed pre-spawn (prep-2), NOT EA-8-closed at Item 4.0. EA-8 only releases MCP server file-locks.

